son\", \"from\": 314, \"to\": 322}, {\"ngram\": \"an empty street\", \"from\": 337, \"to\": 352}, {\"ngram\": \"the opening ceremony\", \"from\": 362, \"to\": 382}]}, {\"sentence\": \"REUTERS/Peter Cziborra/File Photo Published\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:01 AM Updated\\u00c2Jul 27, 2024, 02:01 AM LONDON - With medals made of iron salvaged from Eiffel Tower refurbishments and stadium seating of recycled plastic, Paris 2024 aims to be the greenest olympics yet.\", \"from\": 384, \"to\": 652, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"02:01 AM\", \"from\": 442, \"to\": 450}, {\"ngram\": \"Updated\\u00c2Jul\", \"from\": 451, \"to\": 462}, {\"ngram\": \"02:01 AM\", \"from\": 473, \"to\": 481}, {\"ngram\": \"LONDON\", \"from\": 482, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"medals\", \"from\": 496, \"to\": 502}, {\"ngram\": \"iron\", \"from\": 511, \"to\": 515}, {\"ngram\": \"Eiffel Tower refurbishments\", \"from\": 530, \"to\": 557}, {\"ngram\": \"stadium seating\", \"from\": 562, \"to\": 577}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled plastic\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"the greenest olympics\", \"from\": 621, \"to\": 642}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The case for action is clear as scientists have said intense heat linked to man-made carbon emissions is a growing risk to competitors at the world's largest sporting event and beyond.\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 838, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The case\", \"from\": 654, \"to\": 662}, {\"ngram\": \"action\", \"from\": 667, \"to\": 673}, {\"ngram\": \"scientists\", \"from\": 686, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"intense heat\", \"from\": 707, \"to\": 719}, {\"ngram\": \"man-made carbon emissions\", \"from\": 730, \"to\": 755}, {\"ngram\": \"a growing risk\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 773}, {\"ngram\": \"competitors\", \"from\": 777, \"to\": 788}, {\"ngram\": \"the world's largest sporting event\", \"from\": 792, \"to\": 826}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has pledged to reduce its carbon emissions by half compared to the average emitted during the London and Rio Summer Games.\", \"from\": 840, \"to\": 973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 840, \"end\": 850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 945, \"end\": 951, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9970232970259877, \"rank\": 0.0018852127795279184, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its carbon emissions\", \"from\": 873, \"to\": 893}, {\"ngram\": \"half\", \"from\": 897, \"to\": 901}, {\"ngram\": \"Rio Summer Games\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 972}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here are some of Paris 2024's efforts towards meeting that goal.\", \"from\": 975, \"to\": 1039, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 992, \"end\": 1002, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"that goal\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1038}]}, {\"sentence\": \"CONSTRUCTION For many people, Olympic stadiums such as Rio's Olympic Aquatic Centre that have failed to find a purpose after the Games symbolise extravagance.\", \"from\": 1041, \"to\": 1200, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1097, \"end\": 1100, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"score\": 0.9990859639398125, \"rank\": 0.0007449144730968109, \"text\": \"Rio\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Earth_Summit\"}, {\"begin\": 1103, \"end\": 1125, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"score\": 0.9999998465305115, \"rank\": 1.5346933526662944e-07, \"text\": \"Olympic Aquatic Centre\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Athens_Olympic_Sports_Complex\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many people\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1069}, {\"ngram\": \"a purpose\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1159}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games symbolise extravagance\", \"from\": 1166, \"to\": 1198}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris 2024 has sought to minimise new construction.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1253, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1202, \"end\": 1212, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"new construction\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1252}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Almost all venues use existing or temporary sites, often relying on the city's landmarks as backdrops.\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1357, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Almost all venues\", \"from\": 1255, \"to\": 1272}, {\"ngram\": \"existing or temporary sites\", \"from\": 1277, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"the city's landmarks\", \"from\": 1323, \"to\": 1343}, {\"ngram\": \"backdrops\", \"from\": 1347, \"to\": 1356}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say the replacement of concrete with low carbon building materials, including sustainably-sourced wood, will reduce the Olympic Village's emissions by 30% compared to what the organisers referred to as conventional projects without giving details.\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1617, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1490, \"end\": 1505, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56247232913818e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 1359, \"to\": 1369}, {\"ngram\": \"the replacement\", \"from\": 1374, \"to\": 1389}, {\"ngram\": \"concrete\", \"from\": 1393, \"to\": 1401}, {\"ngram\": \"low carbon building materials\", \"from\": 1407, \"to\": 1436}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainably-sourced wood\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1472}, {\"ngram\": \"30%\", \"from\": 1521, \"to\": 1524}, {\"ngram\": \"the organisers\", \"from\": 1542, \"to\": 1556}, {\"ngram\": \"conventional projects\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1593}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 1609, \"to\": 1616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Permanent infrastructure accounted for 73% of the estimated 467,000 metric tons of carbon emissions generated by the Olympic Games between 2018 and 2023.\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1772, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Permanent infrastructure\", \"from\": 1619, \"to\": 1643}, {\"ngram\": \"73%\", \"from\": 1658, \"to\": 1661}, {\"ngram\": \"the estimated 467,000 metric tons\", \"from\": 1665, \"to\": 1698}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon emissions\", \"from\": 1702, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1732, \"to\": 1749}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In addition, 11,000 seats at the only two purpose-built arenas for Paris 2024 are made out of recycled plastic.\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1885, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1841, \"end\": 1851, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.3488175385531487e-20, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"addition\", \"from\": 1777, \"to\": 1785}, {\"ngram\": \"11,000 seats\", \"from\": 1787, \"to\": 1799}, {\"ngram\": \"the only two purpose-built arenas\", \"from\": 1803, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"recycled plastic\", \"from\": 1868, \"to\": 1884}]}, {\"sentence\": \"TRANSPORT Along with construction, transport is expected to be one of the biggest sources of emissions during the Games.\", \"from\": 1887, \"to\": 2008, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"construction\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1920}, {\"ngram\": \"transport\", \"from\": 1922, \"to\": 1931}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest sources\", \"from\": 1957, \"to\": 1976}, {\"ngram\": \"emissions\", \"from\": 1980, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1997, \"to\": 2006}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers have said they will use low-carbon vehicles to ferry around athletes and official visitors and that all venues are accessible by bike, foot or public transport.\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2181, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 2010, \"to\": 2020}, {\"ngram\": \"low-carbon vehicles\", \"from\": 2045, \"to\": 2064}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2081, \"to\": 2089}, {\"ngram\": \"official visitors\", \"from\": 2094, \"to\": 2111}, {\"ngram\": \"all venues\", \"from\": 2121, \"to\": 2131}, {\"ngram\": \"bike\", \"from\": 2150, \"to\": 2154}, {\"ngram\": \"foot\", \"from\": 2156, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"public transport\", \"from\": 2164, \"to\": 2180}]}, {\"sentence\": \"However, Paris is not tackling the emissions generated by spectators travelling to the Games - such emissions made up almost a third (28%) of the 3.3 million metric tons of carbon emitted by the London 2012 Games.\", \"from\": 2183, \"to\": 2396, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2192, \"end\": 2197, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2626005063133335e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 2378, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"London 2012 Games\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the emissions\", \"from\": 2214, \"to\": 2227}, {\"ngram\": \"spectators\", \"from\": 2241, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 2266, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"such emissions\", \"from\": 2278, \"to\": 2292}, {\"ngram\": \"the 3.3 million metric tons\", \"from\": 2325, \"to\": 2352}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon\", \"from\": 2356, \"to\": 2362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"RENEWABLE POWER Paris 2024 has said its venues will use renewable energy sources via the grid, rather than the diesel-powered generators often used at sporting venues.\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2566, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"RENEWABLE POWER Paris\", \"from\": 2398, \"to\": 2419}, {\"ngram\": \"its venues\", \"from\": 2434, \"to\": 2444}, {\"ngram\": \"renewable energy sources\", \"from\": 2454, \"to\": 2478}, {\"ngram\": \"the grid\", \"from\": 2483, \"to\": 2491}, {\"ngram\": \"the diesel-powered generators\", \"from\": 2505, \"to\": 2534}, {\"ngram\": \"sporting venues\", \"from\": 2549, \"to\": 2564}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Some 5,000 metres squared of solar panels have been installed on the roof of the Aquatics Centre and Olympic Village, and a 400 metre squared floating solar farm set up on the River Seine.\", \"from\": 2568, \"to\": 2756, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2669, \"end\": 2684, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.56247232913818e-16, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 2744, \"end\